**Tasks of the Monitoring Team**

* Work with INTERPOL and Member States to obtain photographs of listed individuals for possible inclusion in INTERPOL Special Notices
* Assist other subsidiary bodies of the Security Council and their expert panels in enhancing cooperation with INTERPOL
* Report to the Committee on a regular basis or when requested on the work of the Monitoring Team
* Report periodically on linkages between Al-Qaida and those eligible for designation under relevant sanctions resolutions

**Tasks of the Office of the Ombudsperson**

* Upon receipt of a delisting request, acknowledge receipt, inform the petitioner of the procedure, answer questions, and verify if the request is new or repeated
* Forward delisting requests to Committee members, designating States, and relevant UN bodies, and ask for additional information within four months
* Engage in dialogue with States to determine their opinions on the delisting request and gather information
* Receive information from the Monitoring Team within four months, including all relevant information available to the Team.
